import { Component } from '@angular/core'; import { HttpClient } from "@angular/common/http"; import { Observable } from "rxjs"; @Component({ selector: 'app-root', templateUrl: './app.component.html', styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'] }) export class AppComponent { title = 'toDoFront'; constructor(private http: HttpClient) {} ngOnInit(){ //this.updateLibros().subscribe(); } tryAdd(){ this.getFrase().subscribe() } tryUpdate(){ this.updateLibros().subscribe() } public getFrase(): Observable { const payload = { "title": "maria1", "text": "111111111" } const url = "https://us-central1-atomchallengetodo.cloudfunctions.net/app/addTask" return this.http.post(url, payload ); } updateLibros(): Observable{ const payload = { "id": "31PS4zMyf3AZfUbrSElw", "title": "mariaEditado", "text": "test" } const url = "https://us-central1-atomchallengetodo.cloudfunctions.net/app/updateTask/"+payload.id return this.http.put(url, payload ); } public getlibros(): Observable { const url = "https://us-central1-atomchallengetodo.cloudfunctions.net/app/guardarLibro" return this.http.get(url); } }
Shiba Inu Dog Breed

The Shiba Inu is the smallest of the six original and distinct spitz breeds of dog from Japan. A small, agile dog that copes very well with mountainous terrain, the Shiba Inu was originally bred for hunting.
